Description: Handle sliver of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine buff-brown.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 110, 32). Name Athanophilos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0040.14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0477)
